            <div1 id="BQ-02-1-0002">
                <p>The Brown University <hi rend="u">Alumni Monthly</hi> for April 1968 has a delightful
two-page article, “Damon’s 2-Day Do,” by Garrett D. Byrnes, reprinted from the Providence 
<hi rend="u">Journal</hi>. <hi rend="u">Los</hi>, a magazine of verse published at Brown, has dedicated its April
issue to Foster; the poems include two from the <hi rend="u">Birthday Garland</hi> and “For Mr. Nomad,”
previously unpublished, by Alvin Rosenfeld.</p>
            </div1>
